{"questionId":"16852","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper forms two chlorides, copper(I) chloride and copper(II) chloride.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Copper(II) chloride is used as a catalyst in the production of chlorine from hydrogen chloride.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">4HCl (g) + O<sub>2</sub> (g) → 2Cl<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2H<sub>2</sub>O (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Calculate the standard enthalpy change, Δ<em>H</em><sup>θ</sup>, in kJ, for this reaction, using section 12 of the data booklet.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Δ<em>H</em><sup>θ</sup> = ΣΔ<em>H</em><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><sup><span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\">θ</span></sup></span><sub>f</sub> (products) − ΣΔ<em>H</em><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><sup><span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\">θ</span></sup></span><sub>f</sub> (reactants) ✔<br>Δ<em>H</em><span style=\"font-size:14px;\"><sup><span style=\"text-align:left;color:#000000;text-indent:0px;letter-spacing:normal;font-family:Verdana , Arial , Helvetica , sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:400;text-decoration:none;display:inline !important;white-space:normal;float:none;background-color:#ffffff;\">θ</span></sup></span> = 2(−241.8 «kJ mol<sup>−1</sup>») − 4(−92.3 «kJ mol<sup>−1</sup>») = −114.4 «kJ» ✔</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"> NOTE:&nbsp;Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"16852","referenceCode":"19N.2.sl.TZ0.5a(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Copper(II) chloride is used as a catalyst in the production of chlorine from hydrogen chloride. 4HCl (g) + O2 (g) → 2Cl2 (g) + 2H2O (g) Calculate the standard enthalpy change, ΔHθ,","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Nature of Science","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.2 Hess’s Law","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}